    "summary": "Opto 22 exposes four documented HTTP integration surfaces for its industrial controller products: groov Manage REST API, groov View REST API, PAC Control REST API for SNAP PAC, and PAC Control REST API on groov EPIC; no public GraphQL, MCP, or CLI surface was found.",
    "description": "Opto 22 makes industrial automation and I/O products including groov EPIC and SNAP PAC controllers. Its developer site documents REST APIs for reading and writing controller I/O, PAC Control variables, files, and groov View data-store tags.",
    "credentials": {
      "groov_api_key": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "groov API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://developer.opto22.com/groov/view/",
        "setup": "Create or open a user in groov and copy that user's API key. For groov View, go to [Getting Started with the groov View REST API](https://developer.opto22.com/groov/view/) and in groov Build choose `Configure > Accounts`, create a user with role `Admin` or `Editor`, then copy the automatically generated API key. For groov EPIC-hosted APIs, open [groov Manage](https://developer.opto22.com/groov/manage/getting-started/), go to the `Accounts` page, select the user, and copy the API key shown there. Use this key for groov Manage, groov View on EPIC, and PAC Control on groov EPIC.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "snap_pac_api_key_basic": {
        "type": "compound",
        "label": "SNAP PAC API key ID and value for Basic auth",
        "generateUrl": "https://developer.opto22.com/rest/pac/api-keys/",
        "setup": "On a SNAP PAC controller, first create the API admin as described in [Getting Started with the PAC Control REST API for SNAP PAC](https://developer.opto22.com/rest/pac/) and its linked setup pages. Then open the controller's Keys API management page as described in [API Keys](https://developer.opto22.com/rest/pac/api-keys/) (example: ``http://<controller-ip>/admin/keys``), sign in as the API administrator, and create at least one enabled key pair: enter a key identifier in `ID`, a secret in `Value`, choose `Read Only` or `Read-Write`, and click `Submit`. When calling the API, send the key `ID` as the HTTP Basic username and the key `Value` as the HTTP Basic password.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
    },
